element_texts.text:
237 Oakwood Blvd.
To Dr. Martezuma: 
My dear Doctor:
Could you have heard 
the kindly words of 
praise spoken of you
and your touching
remarks of this after-
noon I am sure you 
would feel that you 
had done a good
work and given

food for conjecture
as well as great pleasure
to your hearers.
May our Father 
aid you in the work
you have undertaken
and my you (unlike
La Salle) live to see the fruits of your
labor. If in my 
feeble way I can at
any time serve you
please command

me. Thanking you
over an over again
I am sincerely and
gratefully yours,
Janet M. Dickson
(Mrs. N. J.)
June Second 1904
